searchData={"items":[{"type":"task","title":"mix rb.audit_fingerprints","doc":"Recomputes every fingerprint from its associations and reports any row whose\nstored value has drifted from what the current algorithm produces.\n\nFingerprints are denormalised, hand-synced derived state — nothing at the DB\nlevel guarantees they match the associations — so this task is the safety net:\nrun it on demand or on a schedule to detect drift. It exits non-zero when drift\nis found, so it can gate CI.\n\n    mix rb.audit_fingerprints","ref":"Mix.Tasks.Rb.AuditFingerprints.html"},{"type":"task","title":"mix rb.load_data","doc":"Mix task to initialize the repo using a data.csv file in the project's root directory","ref":"Mix.Tasks.Rb.LoadData.html"},{"type":"function","title":"Mix.Tasks.Rb.LoadData.run/1","doc":"Callback implementation for  Mix.Task.run/1 .","ref":"Mix.Tasks.Rb.LoadData.html#run/1"},{"type":"module","title":"RichardBurton","doc":"RichardBurton keeps the contexts that define your domain\nand business logic.\n\nContexts are also responsible for managing your data, regardless\nif it comes from the database, an external API or others.","ref":"RichardBurton.html"},{"type":"behaviour","title":"RichardBurton.Auth","doc":"Authentication/authorization boundary. Delegates to the implementation\nconfigured under `:auth_service` (default `RichardBurton.Auth.Google`, swapped\nfor a Mox mock in tests).","ref":"RichardBurton.Auth.html"},{"type":"callback","title":"RichardBurton.Auth.authorize/2","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.Auth.html#c:authorize/2"},{"type":"callback","title":"RichardBurton.Auth.verify/1","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.Auth.html#c:verify/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Auth.authorize/2","doc":"Returns `:ok` if `subject_id` currently holds `role`, `:error` otherwise.","ref":"RichardBurton.Auth.html#authorize/2"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Auth.verify/1","doc":"Authenticates an ID token, returning `{:ok, subject_id}` or `:error`.","ref":"RichardBurton.Auth.html#verify/1"},{"type":"module","title":"RichardBurton.Auth.Claims","doc":"Validates the claims of an OIDC ID token: issuer, audience, subject and\nexpiry. Signature verification is performed separately (see\n`RichardBurton.Auth.Google`); this module only checks the decoded claims.","ref":"RichardBurton.Auth.Claims.html"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Auth.Claims.validate/4","doc":"Returns `{:ok, subject_id}` when every claim is valid, `:error` otherwise.","ref":"RichardBurton.Auth.Claims.html#validate/4"},{"type":"module","title":"RichardBurton.Auth.Csrf","doc":"Double-submit CSRF token: a signed, session-bound token issued as a readable\n(`http_only: false`) cookie at login and echoed back in the `rb-csrf-token`\nheader on state-changing admin requests (see `RichardBurtonWeb.Plugs.VerifyCsrf`).\n\nIt is signed with the endpoint's `secret_key_base`, so it can't be forged\nwithout the server secret, and it carries the session's subject so a token\nminted for one user can't authorize another's request. Defense in depth on top\nof the `SameSite=Lax` session cookie.","ref":"RichardBurton.Auth.Csrf.html"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Auth.Csrf.header_name/0","doc":"Name of the request header carrying the double-submit CSRF token.","ref":"RichardBurton.Auth.Csrf.html#header_name/0"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Auth.Csrf.sign/1","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.Auth.Csrf.html#sign/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Auth.Csrf.verify/1","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.Auth.Csrf.html#verify/1"},{"type":"module","title":"RichardBurton.Auth.Google","doc":"Google identity-provider implementation of the `RichardBurton.Auth` behaviour.\n\nID tokens are verified against Google's JWKS signing keys, which are cached\nand refreshed by `RichardBurton.Auth.KeyStore` (using the\n`RichardBurton.Auth.JWKS.Google` provider) so that key rotation does not\nrequire a restart. The issuer, audience and expiry are all validated (see\n`RichardBurton.Auth.Claims`).","ref":"RichardBurton.Auth.Google.html"},{"type":"behaviour","title":"RichardBurton.Auth.JWKS","doc":"Behaviour for fetching a JSON Web Key Set (JWKS): the signing keys and issuer\nused to verify ID tokens, plus the cache lifetime the provider advertises.","ref":"RichardBurton.Auth.JWKS.html"},{"type":"type","title":"RichardBurton.Auth.JWKS.result/0","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.Auth.JWKS.html#t:result/0"},{"type":"callback","title":"RichardBurton.Auth.JWKS.fetch/0","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.Auth.JWKS.html#c:fetch/0"},{"type":"module","title":"RichardBurton.Auth.JWKS.Google","doc":"`RichardBurton.Auth.JWKS` implementation that fetches from Google: the issuer\nfrom Google's OpenID configuration and the signing keys from its OAuth2 certs\nendpoint (respecting the certs' `Cache-Control: max-age`).","ref":"RichardBurton.Auth.JWKS.Google.html"},{"type":"module","title":"RichardBurton.Auth.JWKS.Stub","doc":"`RichardBurton.Auth.JWKS` implementation that fetches nothing.\n\nUsed under test (and in any environment where no identity provider is\nconfigured) so the key store can run without making network calls. Any token\nverification against it fails cleanly.","ref":"RichardBurton.Auth.JWKS.Stub.html"},{"type":"module","title":"RichardBurton.Auth.KeyStore","doc":"Caches a provider's JWKS signing keys and keeps them fresh so that key\nrotation does not require restarting the server.\n\nProvider-agnostic: it caches whatever any `RichardBurton.Auth.JWKS`\nimplementation returns. The implementation is configured via the `:jwks_provider`\napplication env and can be overridden per instance with the `:provider` option.\n\nKeys are refreshed:\n\n  * on a schedule, honouring the `max-age` advertised by the provider; and\n  * lazily, whenever a token presents a `kid` that is not currently cached\n    (rate-limited by `:refresh_cooldown` to avoid hammering the\n    provider with bogus `kid`s).","ref":"RichardBurton.Auth.KeyStore.html"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Auth.KeyStore.child_spec/1","doc":"Returns a specification to start this module under a supervisor.\n\nSee `Supervisor`.","ref":"RichardBurton.Auth.KeyStore.html#child_spec/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Auth.KeyStore.fetch_key/2","doc":"Returns `{:ok, key}` for the cached key matching `kid`. On a cache miss, the\nkeys are refreshed once (rate-limited) before giving up with `:error`.","ref":"RichardBurton.Auth.KeyStore.html#fetch_key/2"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Auth.KeyStore.issuer/1","doc":"The issuer advertised by the provider, or nil if not fetched yet.","ref":"RichardBurton.Auth.KeyStore.html#issuer/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Auth.KeyStore.start_link/1","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.Auth.KeyStore.html#start_link/1"},{"type":"behaviour","title":"RichardBurton.Auth.Recaptcha","doc":"Behaviour for recaptcha authorization services","ref":"RichardBurton.Auth.Recaptcha.html"},{"type":"callback","title":"RichardBurton.Auth.Recaptcha.verify/1","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.Auth.Recaptcha.html#c:verify/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Auth.Recaptcha.verify/1","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.Auth.Recaptcha.html#verify/1"},{"type":"module","title":"RichardBurton.Auth.Recaptcha.Google","doc":"Google Recaptcha implementation for RichardBurton.Auth.Recaptcha behaviour","ref":"RichardBurton.Auth.Recaptcha.Google.html"},{"type":"module","title":"RichardBurton.Auth.Session","doc":"Server-side (stateful) app sessions. Each session is a row in `auth_sessions`\nholding the authenticated user's `subject_id` and the SHA-256 hash of an opaque\ntoken. The raw token is set as the `rb-session` cookie and looked up on every\nrequest, so a session can be revoked instantly by deleting its row.\n\nLifetime is a **sliding idle timeout** (`:session_idle_timeout`) refreshed on\nuse, bounded by an **absolute cap** (`:session_max_age`) measured from creation.","ref":"RichardBurton.Auth.Session.html"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Auth.Session.cookie_name/0","doc":"Name of the httpOnly cookie carrying the raw session token.","ref":"RichardBurton.Auth.Session.html#cookie_name/0"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Auth.Session.create/1","doc":"Creates a session for `subject_id`, returning the raw opaque token to set as the cookie.","ref":"RichardBurton.Auth.Session.html#create/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Auth.Session.idle_timeout/0","doc":"Sliding idle timeout in seconds (`:session_idle_timeout`).","ref":"RichardBurton.Auth.Session.html#idle_timeout/0"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Auth.Session.max_age/0","doc":"Absolute session cap in seconds — also the cookie max_age (`:session_max_age`).","ref":"RichardBurton.Auth.Session.html#max_age/0"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Auth.Session.revoke/1","doc":"Revokes the session identified by `token` (deletes its row).","ref":"RichardBurton.Auth.Session.html#revoke/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Auth.Session.revoke_all/1","doc":"Revokes every session for `subject_id` (sign out everywhere).","ref":"RichardBurton.Auth.Session.html#revoke_all/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Auth.Session.verify/1","doc":"Verifies a raw token, returning `{:ok, subject_id}` or `:error`.\n\nRejects (and prunes) sessions past their idle timeout or absolute cap, and\nslides the idle timeout forward on a valid, active session.","ref":"RichardBurton.Auth.Session.html#verify/1"},{"type":"module","title":"RichardBurton.Author","doc":"Schema for authors","ref":"RichardBurton.Author.html"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Author.all/0","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.Author.html#all/0"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Author.fingerprint/1","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.Author.html#fingerprint/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Author.flatten/1","doc":"Join a list of authors back into a comma-separated string. A non-list value\n(already flat) is returned unchanged.","ref":"RichardBurton.Author.html#flatten/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Examples - RichardBurton.Author.flatten/1","doc":"iex> RichardBurton.Author.flatten([%{\"name\" => \"Machado de Assis\"}, %{\"name\" => \"Clarice Lispector\"}])\n  \"Machado de Assis, Clarice Lispector\"\n\n  iex> RichardBurton.Author.flatten(\"Machado de Assis\")\n  \"Machado de Assis\"","ref":"RichardBurton.Author.html#flatten/1-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Author.get_name/1","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.Author.html#get_name/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Author.link/1","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.Author.html#link/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Author.link_fingerprint/1","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.Author.html#link_fingerprint/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Author.maybe_insert!/1","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.Author.html#maybe_insert!/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Author.nest/1","doc":"Split a comma-separated authors string into nested author maps.","ref":"RichardBurton.Author.html#nest/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Examples - RichardBurton.Author.nest/1","doc":"iex> RichardBurton.Author.nest(\"Machado de Assis, Clarice Lispector\")\n  [%{\"name\" => \"Machado de Assis\"}, %{\"name\" => \"Clarice Lispector\"}]","ref":"RichardBurton.Author.html#nest/1-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Author.search/1","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.Author.html#search/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Author.search/2","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.Author.html#search/2"},{"type":"module","title":"RichardBurton.Codec","doc":"Utilities for serialization and deserialization","ref":"RichardBurton.Codec.html"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Codec.flatten/1","doc":"Flattens a nested map, post-processing the resulting `{key, value}` pairs with the given `post` function.\n  Lists are not traversed.\n  Keys on nested maps are regenerated prepending the key of their parent map.\n\n  Returns the flattened map with string keys.","ref":"RichardBurton.Codec.html#flatten/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Examples - RichardBurton.Codec.flatten/1","doc":"iex> RichardBurton.Codec.flatten(%{})\n      %{}\n\n      iex> RichardBurton.Codec.flatten(%{a: 1, b: 2, c: 3})\n      %{\"a\" => 1, \"b\" => 2, \"c\" => 3}\n\n      iex> RichardBurton.Codec.flatten(%{a: [1, 2, %{a: 1}]})\n      %{\"a\" => [1, 2, %{a: 1}]}\n\n      iex> RichardBurton.Codec.flatten(%{a: 1, b: %{a: 1, b: 2, c: 3}})\n      %{\"a\" => 1, \"b_a\" => 1, \"b_b\" => 2, \"b_c\" => 3}\n\n      iex> RichardBurton.Codec.flatten(%{a: 1, b: [2, 3, %{a: 1, b: 2}], c: %{a: 1, b: 2, c: 3}})\n      %{ \"a\" => 1, \"b\" => [2, 3, %{a: 1, b: 2}], \"c_a\" => 1, \"c_b\"=> 2, \"c_c\"=> 3}","ref":"RichardBurton.Codec.html#flatten/1-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Codec.nest/1","doc":"Automatically nests a flat map.\n  Keys are grouped by their Longest Common Prefix (LCP) to define nesting points.\n  LCP is calculated considering atomic words separated by underscore:\n\n    `aBC` and `aDE do not have a common prefix\n    `a_BC` and `a_DE` have \"a\" as common prefix\n    `a_b_BC` and `a_b_DE` have \"a_b\" as common prefix\n\n  Returns the nested map with string keys.","ref":"RichardBurton.Codec.html#nest/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Examples - RichardBurton.Codec.nest/1","doc":"iex> RichardBurton.Codec.nest(%{})\n      %{}\n\n      iex> RichardBurton.Codec.nest(%{a: 1, b: 2, c: 3})\n      %{\"a\" => 1, \"b\" => 2, \"c\" => 3}\n\n      iex> RichardBurton.Codec.nest(%{a: 1, b_a: 1, b_b: 2, b_c: 3})\n      %{\"a\" => 1, \"b\" => %{\"a\" => 1, \"b\" => 2, \"c\" => 3}}\n\n      iex> RichardBurton.Codec.nest(%{a: 1, b_a: 1, b_b: 2, b_c_c: 3})\n      %{\"a\" => 1, \"b\" => %{\"a\" => 1, \"b\" => 2, \"c_c\" => 3}}\n\n      iex> RichardBurton.Codec.nest(%{a: 1, b_a: 1, b_b: 2, b_c_c_c: 3})\n      %{\"a\" => 1, \"b\" => %{\"a\" => 1, \"b\" => 2, \"c_c_c\" => 3}}\n\n      iex> RichardBurton.Codec.nest(%{a: 1, b_a: 1, b_b: 2, b_c_c: 3, b_c_d: 4})\n      %{\"a\" => 1, \"b\" => %{\"a\" => 1, \"b\" => 2, \"c\" => %{\"c\" => 3, \"d\" => 4}}}","ref":"RichardBurton.Codec.html#nest/1-examples"},{"type":"module","title":"RichardBurton.Country","doc":"Schema for countries","ref":"RichardBurton.Country.html"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Country.all/0","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.Country.html#all/0"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Country.fingerprint/1","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.Country.html#fingerprint/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Country.flatten/1","doc":"Join a list of countries back into a comma-separated code string. A non-list\nvalue (already flat) is returned unchanged.","ref":"RichardBurton.Country.html#flatten/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Examples - RichardBurton.Country.flatten/1","doc":"iex> RichardBurton.Country.flatten([%{\"code\" => \"BR\"}, %{\"code\" => \"US\"}])\n  \"BR, US\"\n\n  iex> RichardBurton.Country.flatten(\"BR\")\n  \"BR\"","ref":"RichardBurton.Country.html#flatten/1-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Country.get_code/1","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.Country.html#get_code/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Country.link/1","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.Country.html#link/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Country.link_fingerprint/1","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.Country.html#link_fingerprint/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Country.maybe_insert!/1","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.Country.html#maybe_insert!/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Country.nest/1","doc":"Split a comma-separated country-code string into nested country maps.","ref":"RichardBurton.Country.html#nest/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Examples - RichardBurton.Country.nest/1","doc":"iex> RichardBurton.Country.nest(\"BR, US\")\n  [%{\"code\" => \"BR\"}, %{\"code\" => \"US\"}]","ref":"RichardBurton.Country.html#nest/1-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Country.validate_code/1","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.Country.html#validate_code/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Country.validate_countries/1","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.Country.html#validate_countries/1"},{"type":"module","title":"RichardBurton.Email","doc":"Schema for emails","ref":"RichardBurton.Email.html"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Email.changeset/2","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.Email.html#changeset/2"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Email.contact/1","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.Email.html#contact/1"},{"type":"module","title":"RichardBurton.Fingerprint","doc":"Computes the fingerprints used as composite-identity keys for publications and\ntheir shared associations.\n\nA set-valued attribute (countries, publishers, translators, original authors)\nis collapsed into a single scalar so a Postgres unique constraint can enforce\nset identity — which a many-to-many relationship can't express directly.\n\nAll set fingerprints go through `of_set/1` so the delimiter is defined in one\nplace: without a separator, variable-length values collide (e.g. `[\"AnnBob\"]`\nand `[\"Ann\", \"Bob\"]` both join to `\"AnnBob\"`). The composite-record fingerprints\n(`OriginalBook`/`TranslatedBook`) instead concatenate fixed-width sub-fingerprints,\nwhich is already unambiguous, so they don't use this.","ref":"RichardBurton.Fingerprint.html"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Fingerprint.of_set/1","doc":"Fingerprints an order-independent set of strings.","ref":"RichardBurton.Fingerprint.html#of_set/1"},{"type":"module","title":"RichardBurton.FlatPublication","doc":"Schema for publications","ref":"RichardBurton.FlatPublication.html"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.FlatPublication.all/0","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.FlatPublication.html#all/0"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.FlatPublication.validate/2","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.FlatPublication.html#validate/2"},{"type":"behaviour","title":"RichardBurton.Mailer","doc":"Behaviour for Mailer","ref":"RichardBurton.Mailer.html"},{"type":"callback","title":"RichardBurton.Mailer.send/1","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.Mailer.html#c:send/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Mailer.send/1","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.Mailer.html#send/1"},{"type":"module","title":"RichardBurton.Mailer.SMTP","doc":"STMP implementation for RichardBurton.Mailer behaviour","ref":"RichardBurton.Mailer.SMTP.html"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Mailer.SMTP.deliver/2","doc":"Delivers an email.\n\nIf the email is delivered it returns an `{:ok, result}` tuple. If it fails,\nreturns an `{:error, error}` tuple.","ref":"RichardBurton.Mailer.SMTP.html#deliver/2"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Mailer.SMTP.deliver!/2","doc":"Delivers an email, raises on error.\n\nIf the email is delivered, it returns the result. If it fails, it raises\na `DeliveryError`.","ref":"RichardBurton.Mailer.SMTP.html#deliver!/2"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Mailer.SMTP.deliver_many/2","doc":"Delivers a list of emails.\n\nIt accepts a list of `%Swoosh.Email{}` as its first parameter.","ref":"RichardBurton.Mailer.SMTP.html#deliver_many/2"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Mailer.SMTP.send/1","doc":"Callback implementation for  RichardBurton.Mailer.send/1 .","ref":"RichardBurton.Mailer.SMTP.html#send/1"},{"type":"module","title":"RichardBurton.OriginalBook","doc":"Schema for original books","ref":"RichardBurton.OriginalBook.html"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.OriginalBook.all/0","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.OriginalBook.html#all/0"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.OriginalBook.fingerprint/1","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.OriginalBook.html#fingerprint/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.OriginalBook.link/1","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.OriginalBook.html#link/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.OriginalBook.link_fingerprint/1","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.OriginalBook.html#link_fingerprint/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.OriginalBook.maybe_insert!/1","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.OriginalBook.html#maybe_insert!/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.OriginalBook.preload/1","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.OriginalBook.html#preload/1"},{"type":"module","title":"RichardBurton.Publication","doc":"Schema for publications","ref":"RichardBurton.Publication.html"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Publication.all/0","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.Publication.html#all/0"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Publication.insert/1","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.Publication.html#insert/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Publication.insert_all/1","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.Publication.html#insert_all/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Publication.preload/1","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.Publication.html#preload/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Publication.update/2","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.Publication.html#update/2"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Publication.validate/1","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.Publication.html#validate/1"},{"type":"module","title":"RichardBurton.Publication.Codec","doc":"Serialization and deserialization utilities for publications","ref":"RichardBurton.Publication.Codec.html"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Publication.Codec.flatten/1","doc":"Flatten a nested publication back to flat, string-keyed fields — the inverse of\n`nest/1`. Child lists are joined and the `translated_book` association is lifted\nback to top-level `authors` / `original_title` / `original_authors`. Accepts a\n`Publication` struct, a nested map, a list, or a `%{publication:, errors:}` pair.","ref":"RichardBurton.Publication.Codec.html#flatten/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Examples - RichardBurton.Publication.Codec.flatten/1","doc":"iex> RichardBurton.Publication.Codec.flatten(%{\n  ...>   \"title\" => \"Dom Casmurro\",\n  ...>   \"translated_book\" => %{\n  ...>     \"authors\" => [%{\"name\" => \"Helen Caldwell\"}],\n  ...>     \"original_book\" => %{\n  ...>       \"title\" => \"Dom Casmurro\",\n  ...>       \"authors\" => [%{\"name\" => \"Machado de Assis\"}]\n  ...>     }\n  ...>   }\n  ...> })\n  %{\"authors\" => \"Helen Caldwell\", \"original_authors\" => \"Machado de Assis\", \"original_title\" => \"Dom Casmurro\", \"title\" => \"Dom Casmurro\"}","ref":"RichardBurton.Publication.Codec.html#flatten/1-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Publication.Codec.from_csv/1","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.Publication.Codec.html#from_csv/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Publication.Codec.from_csv!/1","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.Publication.Codec.html#from_csv!/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Publication.Codec.nest/1","doc":"Nest a flat publication — a `FlatPublication` struct, a flat map, or a list of\nthem — into the shape the `Publication` changeset expects: multi-value fields\nbecome child maps, and the `translated_book`/`original_book` fields are\nre-parented under their association.","ref":"RichardBurton.Publication.Codec.html#nest/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Examples - RichardBurton.Publication.Codec.nest/1","doc":"iex> nested =\n  ...>   RichardBurton.Publication.Codec.nest(%{\n  ...>     \"title\" => \"Dom Casmurro\",\n  ...>     \"authors\" => \"Helen Caldwell\",\n  ...>     \"original_title\" => \"Dom Casmurro\",\n  ...>     \"original_authors\" => \"Machado de Assis\"\n  ...>   })\n  iex> nested[\"translated_book\"][\"authors\"]\n  [%{\"name\" => \"Helen Caldwell\"}]\n  iex> nested[\"translated_book\"][\"original_book\"][\"title\"]\n  \"Dom Casmurro\"","ref":"RichardBurton.Publication.Codec.html#nest/1-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Publication.Codec.nest_authors/1","doc":"Nest a comma-separated authors string into author maps — used when building a\ntranslated book's author associations.","ref":"RichardBurton.Publication.Codec.html#nest_authors/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Examples - RichardBurton.Publication.Codec.nest_authors/1","doc":"iex> RichardBurton.Publication.Codec.nest_authors(\"Helen Caldwell, Gregory Rabassa\")\n  [%{\"name\" => \"Helen Caldwell\"}, %{\"name\" => \"Gregory Rabassa\"}]","ref":"RichardBurton.Publication.Codec.html#nest_authors/1-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Publication.Codec.to_csv/1","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.Publication.Codec.html#to_csv/1"},{"type":"module","title":"RichardBurton.Publication.Index","doc":"Interface with the searchable publication index","ref":"RichardBurton.Publication.Index.html"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Publication.Index.all/0","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.Publication.Index.html#all/0"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Publication.Index.all/1","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.Publication.Index.html#all/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Publication.Index.count/0","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.Publication.Index.html#count/0"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Publication.Index.count_header/0","doc":"Name of the response header carrying the index's total count.","ref":"RichardBurton.Publication.Index.html#count_header/0"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Publication.Index.search/1","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.Publication.Index.html#search/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Publication.Index.search/2","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.Publication.Index.html#search/2"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Publication.Index.search_keywords/1","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.Publication.Index.html#search_keywords/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Publication.Index.search_keywords/2","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.Publication.Index.html#search_keywords/2"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Publication.Index.without_references/0","doc":"Publications with no provenance, ordered by id — the stable queue the references\nbackfill steps through.","ref":"RichardBurton.Publication.Index.html#without_references/0"},{"type":"module","title":"RichardBurton.Publication.Index.SearchDocument","doc":"Schema for searchable documents","ref":"RichardBurton.Publication.Index.SearchDocument.html"},{"type":"module","title":"RichardBurton.Publication.Index.SearchKeyword","doc":"Schema for searchable documents","ref":"RichardBurton.Publication.Index.SearchKeyword.html"},{"type":"module","title":"RichardBurton.Publisher","doc":"Schema for publishers","ref":"RichardBurton.Publisher.html"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Publisher.all/0","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.Publisher.html#all/0"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Publisher.fingerprint/1","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.Publisher.html#fingerprint/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Publisher.flatten/1","doc":"Join a list of publishers back into a comma-separated string. A non-list value\n(already flat) is returned unchanged.","ref":"RichardBurton.Publisher.html#flatten/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Examples - RichardBurton.Publisher.flatten/1","doc":"iex> RichardBurton.Publisher.flatten([%{\"name\" => \"Noonday Press\"}, %{\"name\" => \"Penguin\"}])\n  \"Noonday Press, Penguin\"\n\n  iex> RichardBurton.Publisher.flatten(\"Noonday Press\")\n  \"Noonday Press\"","ref":"RichardBurton.Publisher.html#flatten/1-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Publisher.get_name/1","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.Publisher.html#get_name/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Publisher.link/1","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.Publisher.html#link/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Publisher.link_fingerprint/1","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.Publisher.html#link_fingerprint/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Publisher.maybe_insert!/1","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.Publisher.html#maybe_insert!/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Publisher.nest/1","doc":"Split a comma-separated publishers string into nested publisher maps.","ref":"RichardBurton.Publisher.html#nest/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Examples - RichardBurton.Publisher.nest/1","doc":"iex> RichardBurton.Publisher.nest(\"Noonday Press, Penguin\")\n  [%{\"name\" => \"Noonday Press\"}, %{\"name\" => \"Penguin\"}]","ref":"RichardBurton.Publisher.html#nest/1-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Publisher.search/1","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.Publisher.html#search/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Publisher.search/2","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.Publisher.html#search/2"},{"type":"module","title":"RichardBurton.Reference","doc":"Schema for publication references: free-text provenance entries that record how\na publication's data was collected, so a reader can verify the claim. Owned by a\nsingle publication (deleted with it), ordered, and edited inline via the\npublication update path — never shared or deduplicated across publications.","ref":"RichardBurton.Reference.html"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Reference.flatten/1","doc":"Reverse of `nest/1`: an ordered list of the reference strings. Accepts loaded\nchild structs (ordered by `position`) or an already-flat list; anything else\n(nil, `%NotLoaded{}`) flattens to an empty list.","ref":"RichardBurton.Reference.html#flatten/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Examples - RichardBurton.Reference.flatten/1","doc":"iex> RichardBurton.Reference.flatten([\n  ...>   %RichardBurton.Reference{content: \"Second\", position: 1},\n  ...>   %RichardBurton.Reference{content: \"First\", position: 0}\n  ...> ])\n  [\"First\", \"Second\"]\n\n  iex> RichardBurton.Reference.flatten(nil)\n  []","ref":"RichardBurton.Reference.html#flatten/1-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Reference.nest/1","doc":"Turn the flat wire shape (an ordered list of free-text strings) into the nested\nchild maps `cast_assoc(:references)` expects, assigning `position` from order.\nBlank rows are dropped so an empty editor row doesn't fail validation.","ref":"RichardBurton.Reference.html#nest/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Examples - RichardBurton.Reference.nest/1","doc":"iex> RichardBurton.Reference.nest([\"First source\", \"Second source\"])\n  [%{\"content\" => \"First source\", \"position\" => 0}, %{\"content\" => \"Second source\", \"position\" => 1}]\n\n  iex> RichardBurton.Reference.nest([\"A source\", \"  \"])\n  [%{\"content\" => \"A source\", \"position\" => 0}]\n\n  A blank in the middle is dropped and positions stay contiguous — the entry\n  after it is `1`, not `2`:\n\n  iex> RichardBurton.Reference.nest([\"First\", \"\", \"Second\"])\n  [%{\"content\" => \"First\", \"position\" => 0}, %{\"content\" => \"Second\", \"position\" => 1}]\n\n  iex> RichardBurton.Reference.nest(nil)\n  []","ref":"RichardBurton.Reference.html#nest/1-examples"},{"type":"module","title":"RichardBurton.Release","doc":"Used for executing DB release tasks when run in production without Mix\ninstalled.","ref":"RichardBurton.Release.html"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Release.migrate/0","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.Release.html#migrate/0"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Release.rollback/2","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.Release.html#rollback/2"},{"type":"module","title":"RichardBurton.Repo","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.Repo.html"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Repo.aggregate/3","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.aggregate/3 .","ref":"RichardBurton.Repo.html#aggregate/3"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Repo.aggregate/4","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.aggregate/4 .","ref":"RichardBurton.Repo.html#aggregate/4"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Repo.all/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.all/2 .","ref":"RichardBurton.Repo.html#all/2"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Repo.all_by/3","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.all_by/3 .","ref":"RichardBurton.Repo.html#all_by/3"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Repo.checked_out?/0","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.checked_out?/0 .","ref":"RichardBurton.Repo.html#checked_out?/0"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Repo.checkout/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.checkout/2 .","ref":"RichardBurton.Repo.html#checkout/2"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Repo.child_spec/1","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.Repo.html#child_spec/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Repo.config/0","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.config/0 .","ref":"RichardBurton.Repo.html#config/0"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Repo.default_options/1","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.default_options/1 .","ref":"RichardBurton.Repo.html#default_options/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Repo.delete/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.delete/2 .","ref":"RichardBurton.Repo.html#delete/2"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Repo.delete!/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.delete!/2 .","ref":"RichardBurton.Repo.html#delete!/2"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Repo.delete_all/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.delete_all/2 .","ref":"RichardBurton.Repo.html#delete_all/2"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Repo.disconnect_all/2","doc":"Forces all connections in the repo pool to disconnect within the given interval.\n\nOnce this function is called, the pool will disconnect all of its connections\nas they are checked in or as they are pinged. Checked in and idle connections\nwill be randomly disconnected within the given time interval.\n\nIf the connection has a backoff configured (which is the case by default),\ndisconnecting means an attempt at a new connection will be done immediately\nafter, without starting a new process for each connection. However, if backoff\nhas been disabled, the connection process will terminate. In such cases,\ndisconnecting all connections may cause the pool supervisor to restart\ndepending on the max_restarts/max_seconds configuration of the pool,\nso you will want to set those carefully.\n\nIf you need connections to be restarted periodically, set the `:max_lifetime`\noption in your repository configuration instead.","ref":"RichardBurton.Repo.html#disconnect_all/2"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Repo.exists?/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.exists?/2 .","ref":"RichardBurton.Repo.html#exists?/2"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Repo.explain/3","doc":"Executes an EXPLAIN statement or similar for the given query according to its kind and the\nadapter in the given repository.","ref":"RichardBurton.Repo.html#explain/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Examples - RichardBurton.Repo.explain/3","doc":"# Postgres\n    iex> MyRepo.explain(:all, Post)\n    \"Seq Scan on posts p0  (cost=0.00..12.12 rows=1 width=443)\"\n\n    iex> Ecto.Adapters.SQL.explain(Repo, :all, Post)\n    \"Seq Scan on posts p0  (cost=0.00..12.12 rows=1 width=443)\"\n\n    # MySQL\n    iex> MyRepo.explain(:all, from(p in Post, where: p.title == \"title\")) |> IO.puts()\n    +----+-------------+-------+------------+------+---------------+------+---------+------+------+----------+-------------+\n    | id | select_type | table | partitions | type | possible_keys | key  | key_len | ref  | rows | filtered | Extra       |\n    +----+-------------+-------+------------+------+---------------+------+---------+------+------+----------+-------------+\n    |  1 | SIMPLE      | p0    | NULL       | ALL  | NULL          | NULL | NULL    | NULL |    1 |    100.0 | Using where |\n    +----+-------------+-------+------------+------+---------------+------+---------+------+------+----------+-------------+\n\n    # Shared opts\n    iex> MyRepo.explain(:all, Post, analyze: true, timeout: 20_000)\n    \"Seq Scan on posts p0  (cost=0.00..11.70 rows=170 width=443) (actual time=0.013..0.013 rows=0 loops=1)\\nPlanning Time: 0.031 ms\\nExecution Time: 0.021 ms\"\n\nIt's safe to execute it for updates and deletes, no data change will be committed:\n\n    iex> MyRepo.explain(Repo, :update_all, from(p in Post, update: [set: [title: \"new title\"]]))\n    \"Update on posts p0  (cost=0.00..11.70 rows=170 width=449)\\n  ->  Seq Scan on posts p0  (cost=0.00..11.70 rows=170 width=449)\"\n\nThis function is also available under the repository with name `explain`:\n\n    iex> MyRepo.explain(:all, from(p in Post, where: p.title == \"title\"))\n    \"Seq Scan on posts p0  (cost=0.00..12.12 rows=1 width=443)\\n  Filter: ((title)::text = 'title'::text)\"","ref":"RichardBurton.Repo.html#explain/3-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"Options - RichardBurton.Repo.explain/3","doc":"Built-in adapters support passing `opts` to the EXPLAIN statement according to the following:\n\nAdapter          | Supported opts\n---------------- | --------------\nPostgrex         | `analyze`, `verbose`, `costs`, `settings`, `buffers`, `timing`, `summary`, `format`, `plan`, `wrap_in_transaction`\nMyXQL            | `format`, `wrap_in_transaction`\n\nAll options except `format` are boolean valued and default to `false`.\n\nThe allowed `format` values are `:map`, `:yaml`, and `:text`:\n  * `:map` is the deserialized JSON encoding.\n  * `:yaml` and `:text` return the result as a string.\n\nThe built-in adapters support the following formats:\n  * Postgrex: `:map`, `:yaml` and `:text`\n  * MyXQL: `:map` and `:text`\n\nThe `wrap_in_transaction` option is a boolean that controls whether the command is run inside of a\ntransaction that is rolled back. This is useful when, for example, you'd like to use `analyze: true`\non an update or delete query without modifying data. Defaults to `true`.\n\nThe `:plan` option in Postgrex can take the values `:custom` or `:fallback_generic`. When `:custom`\nis specified, the explain plan generated will consider the specific values of the query parameters\nthat are supplied. When using `:fallback_generic`, the specific values of the query parameters will\nbe ignored. `:fallback_generic` does not use PostgreSQL's built-in support for a generic explain\nplan (available as of PostgreSQL 16), but instead uses a special implementation that works for PostgreSQL\nversions 12 and above. Defaults to `:custom`.\n\nAny other value passed to `opts` will be forwarded to the underlying adapter query function, including\nshared Repo options such as `:timeout`. Non built-in adapters may have specific behaviour and you should\nconsult their documentation for more details.\n\nFor version compatibility, please check your database's documentation:\n\n  * _Postgrex_: [PostgreSQL doc](https://www.postgresql.org/docs/current/sql-explain.html).\n  * _MyXQL_: [MySQL doc](https://dev.mysql.com/doc/refman/8.0/en/explain.html).","ref":"RichardBurton.Repo.html#explain/3-options"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Repo.get/3","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.get/3 .","ref":"RichardBurton.Repo.html#get/3"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Repo.get!/3","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.get!/3 .","ref":"RichardBurton.Repo.html#get!/3"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Repo.get_by/3","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.get_by/3 .","ref":"RichardBurton.Repo.html#get_by/3"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Repo.get_by!/3","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.get_by!/3 .","ref":"RichardBurton.Repo.html#get_by!/3"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Repo.get_dynamic_repo/0","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.get_dynamic_repo/0 .","ref":"RichardBurton.Repo.html#get_dynamic_repo/0"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Repo.get_unique_key_values/2","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.Repo.html#get_unique_key_values/2"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Repo.in_transaction?/0","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.in_transaction?/0 .","ref":"RichardBurton.Repo.html#in_transaction?/0"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Repo.insert/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.insert/2 .","ref":"RichardBurton.Repo.html#insert/2"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Repo.insert!/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.insert!/2 .","ref":"RichardBurton.Repo.html#insert!/2"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Repo.insert_all/3","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.insert_all/3 .","ref":"RichardBurton.Repo.html#insert_all/3"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Repo.insert_or_update/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.insert_or_update/2 .","ref":"RichardBurton.Repo.html#insert_or_update/2"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Repo.insert_or_update!/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.insert_or_update!/2 .","ref":"RichardBurton.Repo.html#insert_or_update!/2"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Repo.load/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.load/2 .","ref":"RichardBurton.Repo.html#load/2"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Repo.maybe_insert!/2","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.Repo.html#maybe_insert!/2"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Repo.one/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.one/2 .","ref":"RichardBurton.Repo.html#one/2"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Repo.one!/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.one!/2 .","ref":"RichardBurton.Repo.html#one!/2"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Repo.preload/3","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.preload/3 .","ref":"RichardBurton.Repo.html#preload/3"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Repo.prepare_query/3","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.prepare_query/3 .","ref":"RichardBurton.Repo.html#prepare_query/3"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Repo.prepare_transaction/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.prepare_transaction/2 .","ref":"RichardBurton.Repo.html#prepare_transaction/2"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Repo.put_dynamic_repo/1","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.put_dynamic_repo/1 .","ref":"RichardBurton.Repo.html#put_dynamic_repo/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Repo.query/3","doc":"Runs a custom SQL query.\n\nIf the query was successful, it will return an `:ok` tuple containing\na map with at least two keys:\n\n  * `:num_rows` - the number of rows affected\n  * `:rows` - the result set as a list. `nil` may be returned\n    instead of the list if the command does not yield any row\n    as result (but still yields the number of affected rows,\n    like a `delete` command without returning would)","ref":"RichardBurton.Repo.html#query/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Options - RichardBurton.Repo.query/3","doc":"* `:log` - When false, does not log the query\n  * `:timeout` - Execute request timeout, accepts: `:infinity` (default: `15000`);","ref":"RichardBurton.Repo.html#query/3-options"},{"type":"function","title":"Examples - RichardBurton.Repo.query/3","doc":"iex> MyRepo.query(\"SELECT $1::integer + $2\", [40, 2])\n    {:ok, %{rows: [[42]], num_rows: 1}}\n\n    iex> Ecto.Adapters.SQL.query(MyRepo, \"SELECT $1::integer + $2\", [40, 2])\n    {:ok, %{rows: [[42]], num_rows: 1}}","ref":"RichardBurton.Repo.html#query/3-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Repo.query!/3","doc":"Same as `query/3` but returns result directly without `:ok` tuple\nand raises on invalid queries","ref":"RichardBurton.Repo.html#query!/3"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Repo.query_many/3","doc":"Runs a custom SQL query that returns multiple results on the given repo.\n\nIn case of success, it must return an `:ok` tuple containing a list of\nmaps with at least two keys:\n\n  * `:num_rows` - the number of rows affected\n\n  * `:rows` - the result set as a list. `nil` may be returned\n    instead of the list if the command does not yield any row\n    as result (but still yields the number of affected rows,\n    like a `delete` command without returning would)","ref":"RichardBurton.Repo.html#query_many/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Options - RichardBurton.Repo.query_many/3","doc":"* `:log` - When false, does not log the query\n  * `:timeout` - Execute request timeout, accepts: `:infinity` (default: `15000`);","ref":"RichardBurton.Repo.html#query_many/3-options"},{"type":"function","title":"Examples - RichardBurton.Repo.query_many/3","doc":"iex> MyRepo.query_many(\"SELECT $1; SELECT $2;\", [40, 2])\n    {:ok, [%{rows: [[40]], num_rows: 1}, %{rows: [[2]], num_rows: 1}]}\n\n    iex> Ecto.Adapters.SQL.query_many(MyRepo, \"SELECT $1; SELECT $2;\", [40, 2])\n    {:ok, [%{rows: [[40]], num_rows: 1}, %{rows: [[2]], num_rows: 1}]}","ref":"RichardBurton.Repo.html#query_many/3-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Repo.query_many!/3","doc":"Same as `query_many/4` but returns result directly without `:ok` tuple\nand raises on invalid queries","ref":"RichardBurton.Repo.html#query_many!/3"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Repo.reload/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.reload/2 .","ref":"RichardBurton.Repo.html#reload/2"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Repo.reload!/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.reload!/2 .","ref":"RichardBurton.Repo.html#reload!/2"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Repo.rollback/1","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.rollback/1 .","ref":"RichardBurton.Repo.html#rollback/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Repo.start_link/1","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.start_link/1 .","ref":"RichardBurton.Repo.html#start_link/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Repo.stop/1","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.stop/1 .","ref":"RichardBurton.Repo.html#stop/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Repo.stream/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.stream/2 .","ref":"RichardBurton.Repo.html#stream/2"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Repo.to_sql/3","doc":"Converts the given query to SQL according to its kind and the\nadapter in the given repository.","ref":"RichardBurton.Repo.html#to_sql/3"},{"type":"function","title":"Examples - RichardBurton.Repo.to_sql/3","doc":"The examples below are meant for reference. Each adapter will\nreturn a different result:\n\n    iex> MyRepo.to_sql(:all, Post)\n    {\"SELECT p.id, p.title, p.inserted_at, p.created_at FROM posts as p\", []}\n\n    iex> MyRepo.to_sql(:update_all, from(p in Post, update: [set: [title: ^\"hello\"]]))\n    {\"UPDATE posts AS p SET title = $1\", [\"hello\"]}\n\n    iex> Ecto.Adapters.SQL.to_sql(:all, MyRepo, Post)\n    {\"SELECT p.id, p.title, p.inserted_at, p.created_at FROM posts as p\", []}","ref":"RichardBurton.Repo.html#to_sql/3-examples"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Repo.transact/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.transact/2 .","ref":"RichardBurton.Repo.html#transact/2"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Repo.transaction/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.transaction/2 .","ref":"RichardBurton.Repo.html#transaction/2"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Repo.update/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.update/2 .","ref":"RichardBurton.Repo.html#update/2"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Repo.update!/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.update!/2 .","ref":"RichardBurton.Repo.html#update!/2"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Repo.update_all/3","doc":"Callback implementation for  Ecto.Repo.update_all/3 .","ref":"RichardBurton.Repo.html#update_all/3"},{"type":"module","title":"RichardBurton.TranslatedBook","doc":"Schema for translated books","ref":"RichardBurton.TranslatedBook.html"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.TranslatedBook.all/0","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.TranslatedBook.html#all/0"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.TranslatedBook.fingerprint/1","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.TranslatedBook.html#fingerprint/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.TranslatedBook.link/1","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.TranslatedBook.html#link/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.TranslatedBook.link_fingerprint/1","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.TranslatedBook.html#link_fingerprint/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.TranslatedBook.maybe_insert!/1","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.TranslatedBook.html#maybe_insert!/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.TranslatedBook.preload/1","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.TranslatedBook.html#preload/1"},{"type":"module","title":"RichardBurton.User","doc":"Schema for users","ref":"RichardBurton.User.html"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.User.all/0","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.User.html#all/0"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.User.get/1","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.User.html#get/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.User.insert/1","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.User.html#insert/1"},{"type":"module","title":"RichardBurton.Util","doc":"Utilities for general purpose","ref":"RichardBurton.Util.html"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Util.create_fingerprint/1","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.Util.html#create_fingerprint/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Util.deep_merge_maps/2","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.Util.html#deep_merge_maps/2"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Util.stringify_keys/1","doc":"Given an enumerable with atom keys, return the enumerable with string keys instead.\n  Works for keyword lists, key-value tuples, maps and structs.\n  When an ordinary list is given, it stringify the keys of its elements.\n  Does not traverse structures other than ordinary lists.","ref":"RichardBurton.Util.html#stringify_keys/1"},{"type":"function","title":"Examples - RichardBurton.Util.stringify_keys/1","doc":"iex> RichardBurton.Util.stringify_keys(%{})\n      %{}\n\n      iex> RichardBurton.Util.stringify_keys(%{\"key\" => \"value\"})\n      %{\"key\" => \"value\"}\n\n      iex> RichardBurton.Util.stringify_keys({\"key\", \"value\"})\n      {\"key\", \"value\"}\n\n      iex> RichardBurton.Util.stringify_keys([])\n      []\n\n      iex> RichardBurton.Util.stringify_keys({:key, \"value\"})\n      {\"key\", \"value\"}\n\n      iex> RichardBurton.Util.stringify_keys({:key, :value})\n      {\"key\", :value}\n\n      iex> RichardBurton.Util.stringify_keys([key1: \"value\", key2: 1234])\n      [{\"key1\", \"value\"}, {\"key2\", 1234}]\n\n      iex> RichardBurton.Util.stringify_keys([key: :value])\n      [{\"key\", :value}]\n\n      iex> RichardBurton.Util.stringify_keys([{:key1, \"value\"}, {:key2, 1234}])\n      [{\"key1\", \"value\"}, {\"key2\", 1234}]\n\n      iex> RichardBurton.Util.stringify_keys([{:key1, \"value\"}, {\"key2\", 1234}])\n      [{\"key1\", \"value\"}, {\"key2\", 1234}]\n\n      iex> RichardBurton.Util.stringify_keys(%{key1: \"value\", key2: 1234})\n      %{\"key1\" => \"value\", \"key2\" => 1234}\n\n      iex> RichardBurton.Util.stringify_keys(%{key: :value})\n      %{\"key\" => :value}\n\n      iex> RichardBurton.Util.stringify_keys(%{:key1 => \"value\", \"key2\" => 1234})\n      %{\"key1\" => \"value\", \"key2\" => 1234}\n\n      iex> RichardBurton.Util.stringify_keys([{:key1, \"value\"}, %{key2: 1234}])\n      [{\"key1\", \"value\"}, %{\"key2\" => 1234}]\n\n      iex> RichardBurton.Util.stringify_keys(%{key: {:key, \"value\"}})\n      %{\"key\" => {:key, \"value\"}}","ref":"RichardBurton.Util.html#stringify_keys/1-examples"},{"type":"module","title":"RichardBurton.Validation","doc":"Utilities for data validation","ref":"RichardBurton.Validation.html"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Validation.get_errors/1","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.Validation.html#get_errors/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurton.Validation.validate/2","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurton.Validation.html#validate/2"},{"type":"module","title":"RichardBurtonWeb","doc":"The entrypoint for defining your web interface, such\nas controllers, views, channels and so on.\n\nThis can be used in your application as:\n\n    use RichardBurtonWeb, :controller\n    use RichardBurtonWeb, :view\n\nThe definitions below will be executed for every view,\ncontroller, etc, so keep them short and clean, focused\non imports, uses and aliases.\n\nDo NOT define functions inside the quoted expressions\nbelow. Instead, define any helper function in modules\nand import those modules here.","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.html"},{"type":"macro","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.__using__/1","doc":"When used, dispatch to the appropriate controller/view/etc.","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.html#__using__/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.channel/0","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.html#channel/0"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.controller/0","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.html#controller/0"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.router/0","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.html#router/0"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.view/0","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.html#view/0"},{"type":"module","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.AuthorController","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.AuthorController.html"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.AuthorController.index/2","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.AuthorController.html#index/2"},{"type":"module","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.DevSessionController","doc":"Dev/test-only credentials provider. Mints an admin `rb-session` (plus the\nreadable `csrf-token`) without the Google OAuth handshake, so the admin UI can\nbe exercised locally.\n\nKept out of production two ways: this file lives outside `lib/`, on a compile\npath only added for `:dev`/`:test` (see `elixirc_paths` in `mix.exs`), so the\nmodule is not compiled into a prod release at all; and the route is wired only\nwhen `Mix.env() in [:dev, :test]` (see the router).","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.DevSessionController.html"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.DevSessionController.create/2","doc":"Upserts the dev admin user and sets the session cookies for it.","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.DevSessionController.html#create/2"},{"type":"module","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.EmailController","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.EmailController.html"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.EmailController.contact/2","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.EmailController.html#contact/2"},{"type":"module","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.Endpoint","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.Endpoint.html"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.Endpoint.broadcast/3","doc":"Callback implementation for  Phoenix.Endpoint.broadcast/3 .","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.Endpoint.html#broadcast/3"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.Endpoint.broadcast!/3","doc":"Callback implementation for  Phoenix.Endpoint.broadcast!/3 .","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.Endpoint.html#broadcast!/3"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.Endpoint.broadcast_from/4","doc":"Callback implementation for  Phoenix.Endpoint.broadcast_from/4 .","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.Endpoint.html#broadcast_from/4"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.Endpoint.broadcast_from!/4","doc":"Callback implementation for  Phoenix.Endpoint.broadcast_from!/4 .","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.Endpoint.html#broadcast_from!/4"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.Endpoint.call/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Plug.call/2 .","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.Endpoint.html#call/2"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.Endpoint.child_spec/1","doc":"Returns the child specification to start the endpoint\nunder a supervision tree.","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.Endpoint.html#child_spec/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.Endpoint.config/2","doc":"Returns the endpoint configuration for `key`\n\nReturns `default` if the key does not exist.","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.Endpoint.html#config/2"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.Endpoint.config_change/2","doc":"Reloads the configuration given the application environment changes.","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.Endpoint.html#config_change/2"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.Endpoint.host/0","doc":"Returns the host for the given endpoint.","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.Endpoint.html#host/0"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.Endpoint.init/1","doc":"Callback implementation for  Plug.init/1 .","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.Endpoint.html#init/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.Endpoint.local_broadcast/3","doc":"Callback implementation for  Phoenix.Endpoint.local_broadcast/3 .","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.Endpoint.html#local_broadcast/3"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.Endpoint.local_broadcast_from/4","doc":"Callback implementation for  Phoenix.Endpoint.local_broadcast_from/4 .","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.Endpoint.html#local_broadcast_from/4"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.Endpoint.path/1","doc":"Generates the path information when routing to this endpoint.","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.Endpoint.html#path/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.Endpoint.script_name/0","doc":"Generates the script name.","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.Endpoint.html#script_name/0"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.Endpoint.server_info/1","doc":"Returns the address and port that the server is running on","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.Endpoint.html#server_info/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.Endpoint.start_link/1","doc":"Starts the endpoint supervision tree.\n\nAll other options are merged into the endpoint configuration.","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.Endpoint.html#start_link/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.Endpoint.static_integrity/1","doc":"Generates a base64-encoded cryptographic hash (sha512) to a static file\nin `priv/static`. Meant to be used for Subresource Integrity with CDNs.","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.Endpoint.html#static_integrity/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.Endpoint.static_lookup/1","doc":"Returns a two item tuple with the first item being the `static_path`\nand the second item being the `static_integrity`.","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.Endpoint.html#static_lookup/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.Endpoint.static_path/1","doc":"Generates a route to a static file in `priv/static`.","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.Endpoint.html#static_path/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.Endpoint.static_url/0","doc":"Generates the static URL without any path information.\n\nIt uses the configuration under `:static_url` to generate\nsuch. It falls back to `:url` if `:static_url` is not set.","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.Endpoint.html#static_url/0"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.Endpoint.struct_url/0","doc":"Generates the endpoint base URL but as a `URI` struct.\n\nIt uses the configuration under `:url` to generate such.\nUseful for manipulating the URL data and passing it to\nURL helpers.","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.Endpoint.html#struct_url/0"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.Endpoint.subscribe/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Phoenix.Endpoint.subscribe/2 .","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.Endpoint.html#subscribe/2"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.Endpoint.unsubscribe/1","doc":"Callback implementation for  Phoenix.Endpoint.unsubscribe/1 .","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.Endpoint.html#unsubscribe/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.Endpoint.url/0","doc":"Generates the endpoint base URL without any path information.\n\nIt uses the configuration under `:url` to generate such.","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.Endpoint.html#url/0"},{"type":"module","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.ErrorHelpers","doc":"Conveniences for translating and building error messages.","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.ErrorHelpers.html"},{"type":"module","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.ErrorView","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.ErrorView.html"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.ErrorView.__resource__/0","doc":"The resource name, as an atom, for this view","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.ErrorView.html#__resource__/0"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.ErrorView.render/2","doc":"Renders the given template locally.","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.ErrorView.html#render/2"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.ErrorView.template_not_found/2","doc":"Callback invoked when no template is found.\nBy default it raises but can be customized\nto render a particular template.","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.ErrorView.html#template_not_found/2"},{"type":"module","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.Plugs.Authenticate.Bearer","doc":"Authenticates a request via an identity-provider token in the\n`Authorization: Bearer` header (see `RichardBurton.Auth`) and assigns\n`:subject_id`. Used by the login endpoints that exchange the provider token\nfor a session.","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.Plugs.Authenticate.Bearer.html"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.Plugs.Authenticate.Bearer.call/2","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.Plugs.Authenticate.Bearer.html#call/2"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.Plugs.Authenticate.Bearer.init/1","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.Plugs.Authenticate.Bearer.html#init/1"},{"type":"module","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.Plugs.Authenticate.Cookie","doc":"Authenticates a request via the app's own `rb-session` cookie\n(see `RichardBurton.Auth.Session`) and assigns `:subject_id`.","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.Plugs.Authenticate.Cookie.html"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.Plugs.Authenticate.Cookie.call/2","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.Plugs.Authenticate.Cookie.html#call/2"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.Plugs.Authenticate.Cookie.init/1","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.Plugs.Authenticate.Cookie.html#init/1"},{"type":"module","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.Plugs.Authorize.Admin","doc":"Authorizes the request only if the authenticated subject (assigned by an\n`Authenticate` plug) has the `:admin` role.","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.Plugs.Authorize.Admin.html"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.Plugs.Authorize.Admin.call/2","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.Plugs.Authorize.Admin.html#call/2"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.Plugs.Authorize.Admin.init/1","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.Plugs.Authorize.Admin.html#init/1"},{"type":"module","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.Plugs.Authorize.Recaptcha","doc":"Plug for recaptcha verification","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.Plugs.Authorize.Recaptcha.html"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.Plugs.Authorize.Recaptcha.call/2","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.Plugs.Authorize.Recaptcha.html#call/2"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.Plugs.Authorize.Recaptcha.init/1","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.Plugs.Authorize.Recaptcha.html#init/1"},{"type":"module","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.Plugs.VerifyCsrf","doc":"Double-submit CSRF check for state-changing admin requests. Safe methods\n(GET/HEAD/OPTIONS) pass through untouched. For unsafe methods it requires an\n`rb-csrf-token` header carrying a valid `RichardBurton.Auth.Csrf` token whose\nsubject matches the authenticated session (assigned by `Authenticate.Cookie`,\nwhich must run first). Defense in depth on top of the `SameSite=Lax` cookie.","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.Plugs.VerifyCsrf.html"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.Plugs.VerifyCsrf.call/2","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.Plugs.VerifyCsrf.html#call/2"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.Plugs.VerifyCsrf.init/1","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.Plugs.VerifyCsrf.html#init/1"},{"type":"module","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.PublicationController","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.PublicationController.html"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.PublicationController.create_all/2","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.PublicationController.html#create_all/2"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.PublicationController.export/2","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.PublicationController.html#export/2"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.PublicationController.index/2","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.PublicationController.html#index/2"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.PublicationController.update/2","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.PublicationController.html#update/2"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.PublicationController.validate/2","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.PublicationController.html#validate/2"},{"type":"module","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.PublisherController","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.PublisherController.html"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.PublisherController.index/2","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.PublisherController.html#index/2"},{"type":"module","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.Router","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.Router.html"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.Router.api/2","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.Router.html#api/2"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.Router.authenticate_bearer/2","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.Router.html#authenticate_bearer/2"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.Router.authorize_admin/2","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.Router.html#authorize_admin/2"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.Router.authorize_recaptcha/2","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.Router.html#authorize_recaptcha/2"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.Router.call/2","doc":"Callback invoked by Plug on every request.","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.Router.html#call/2"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.Router.files/2","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.Router.html#files/2"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.Router.formatted_routes/1","doc":"Callback implementation for  Phoenix.VerifiedRoutes.formatted_routes/1 .","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.Router.html#formatted_routes/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.Router.init/1","doc":"Callback required by Plug that initializes the router\nfor serving web requests.","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.Router.html#init/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.Router.verified_route?/2","doc":"Callback implementation for  Phoenix.VerifiedRoutes.verified_route?/2 .","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.Router.html#verified_route?/2"},{"type":"module","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.SessionController","doc":"Exchanges a verified identity-provider token for the app's own session cookie.\n\nThe `Authenticate` plug has already verified the incoming provider token and\nassigned `:subject_id`; this action upserts the user and sets the `rb-session`\ncookie so subsequent requests authenticate without forwarding the provider\ntoken.","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.SessionController.html"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.SessionController.create/2","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.SessionController.html#create/2"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.SessionController.delete/2","doc":"Clears the `rb-session` cookie so the browser is signed out. The cookie is\nhttp-only, so only a server response can expire it; no auth is required since\nclearing one's own cookie is harmless.","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.SessionController.html#delete/2"},{"type":"module","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.UserController","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.UserController.html"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.UserController.create/1","doc":"","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.UserController.html#create/1"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.UserController.create/2","doc":"Upserts the user for the verified provider subject (assigned by the bearer\nplug). Login itself goes through `POST /sessions`; this endpoint is kept for\nthe planned admin user-management dashboard (see roadmap 12).","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.UserController.html#create/2"},{"type":"function","title":"RichardBurtonWeb.UserController.me/2","doc":"Returns the current user for a valid `rb-session` cookie, or `null`. Public\n(reads the cookie itself) so the SPA can poll auth state without a 401.","ref":"RichardBurtonWeb.UserController.html#me/2"}],"content_type":"text/markdown","proglang":"elixir","producer":{"name":"ex_doc","version":"0.40.3"}}